Reasoning: The paper proposes new techniques for load-balancing in dense matrix factorizations, which is a common problem in numerical linear algebra. The paper also introduces a new malleable thread-level implementation of BLAS. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MS (Mathematical Software). The paper also discusses parallelization and optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SC (Scientific Computing). The use of BLAS and dense matrix factorizations suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.PF (Performance) as possible sub-categories.
